        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 20 at 4:51PM EDT by NWS Columbia SC</headline>
        <description>At 450 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Villages at Sandhill, or near Dentsville, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Columbia, Forest Acres, Dentsville, Woodfield, Sesquicentennial State
Park, Lake Carolina, Elgin, Killian, Villages at Sandhill, Fort
Jackson, and Fort Jackson Wildcat Road.

This includes the following highways...
Interstate 20 in South Carolina between mile markers 74 and 87.
Interstate 77 between mile markers 15 and 21.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
